{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_28b5fbb4bffe94OzzmB6XrWMxR","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d74a058f1001ouX752mFb0yAsB","parts":[{"id":"prt_d74a062b6001sgYdDblxSN0UKL","messageID":"msg_d74a058f1001ouX752mFb0yAsB","sessionID":"ses_28b5fbb4bffe94OzzmB6XrWMxR","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_69b13d594453421782469f96","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md"},"output":"<path>/workspace/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # Trafilatura: Discover and Extract Text Data on the Web\n2: \n3: <br/>\n4: \n5: <img alt=\"Trafilatura Logo\" src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/adbar/trafilatura/master/docs/trafilatura-logo.png\" align=\"center\" width=\"60%\"/>\n6: \n7: <br/>\n8: \n9: [![Python package](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/trafilatura.svg)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/trafilatura)\n10: [![Python versions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/trafilatura.svg)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/trafilatura)\n11: [![Documentation Status](https://readthedocs.org/projects/trafilatura/badge/?version=latest)](http://trafilatura.readthedocs.org/en/latest/?badge=latest)\n12: [![Code Coverage](https://img.shields.io/codecov/c/github/adbar/trafilatura.svg)](https://codecov.io/gh/adbar/trafilatura)\n13: [![Downloads](https://static.pepy.tech/badge/trafilatura/month)](https://pepy.tech/project/trafilatura)\n14: [![Reference DOI: 10.18653/v1/2021.acl-demo.15](https://img.shields.io/badge/DOI-10.18653%2Fv1%2F2021.acl--demo.15-blue)](https://aclanthology.org/2021.acl-demo.15/)\n15: \n16: <br/>\n17: \n18: <img alt=\"Demo as GIF image\" src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/adbar/trafilatura/master/docs/trafilatura-demo.gif\" align=\"center\" width=\"80%\"/>\n19: \n20: <br/>\n21: \n22: \n23: ## Introduction\n24: \n25: Trafilatura is a cutting-edge **Python package and command-line tool**\n26: designed to **gather text on the Web and simplify the process of turning\n27: raw HTML into structured, meaningful data**. It includes all necessary\n28: discovery and text processing components to perform **web crawling,\n29: downloads, scraping, and extraction** of main texts, metadata and\n30: comments. It aims at staying **handy and modular**: no database is\n31: required, the output can be converted to commonly used formats.\n32: \n33: Going from HTML bulk to essential parts can alleviate many problems\n34: related to text quality, by **focusing on the actual content**,\n35: **avoiding the noise** caused by recurring elements like headers and footers\n36: and by **making sense of the data and metadata** with selected information.\n37: The extractor strikes a balance between limiting noise (precision) and\n38: including all valid parts (recall). It is **robust and reasonably fast**.\n39: \n40: Trafilatura is [widely used](https://trafilatura.readthedocs.io/en/latest/used-by.html)\n41: and integrated into [thousands of projects](https://github.com/adbar/trafilatura/network/dependents)\n42: by companies like HuggingFace, IBM, and Microsoft Research as well as institutions like\n43: the Allen Institute, Stanford, the Tokyo Institute of Technology, and\n44: the University of Munich.\n45: \n46: \n47: ### Features\n48: \n49: - Advanced web crawling and text discovery:\n50:    - Support for sitemaps (TXT, XML) and feeds (ATOM, JSON, RSS)\n51:    - Smart crawling and URL management (filtering and deduplication)\n52: \n53: - Parallel processing of online and offline input:\n54:    - Live URLs, efficient and polite processing of download queues\n55:    - Previously downloaded HTML files and parsed HTML trees\n56: \n57: - Robust and configurable extraction of key elements:\n58:    - Main text (common patterns and generic algorithms like jusText and readability)\n59:    - Metadata (title, author, date, site name, categories and tags)\n60:    - Formatting and structure: paragraphs, titles, lists, quotes, code, line breaks, in-line text formatting\n61:    - Optional elements: comments, links, images, tables\n62: \n63: - Multiple output formats:\n64:    - TXT and Markdown\n65:    - CSV\n66:    - JSON\n67:    - HTML, XML and [XML-TEI](https://tei-c.org/)\n68: \n69: - Optional add-ons:\n70:    - Language detection on extracted content\n71:    - Speed optimizations\n72: \n73: - Actively maintained with support from the open-source community:\n74:    - Regular updates, feature additions, and optimizations\n75:    - Comprehensive documentation\n76: \n77: \n78: ### Evaluation and alternatives\n79: \n80: Trafilatura consistently outperforms other open-source libraries in text\n81: extraction benchmarks, showcasing its efficiency and accuracy in\n82: extracting web content. The extractor tries to strike a balance between\n83: limiting noise and including all valid parts.\n84: \n85: For more information see the [benchmark section](https://trafilatura.readthedocs.io/en/latest/evaluation.html)\n86: and the [evaluation readme](https://github.com/adbar/trafilatura/blob/master/tests/README.rst)\n87: to run the evaluation with the latest data and packages.\n88: \n89: \n90: #### Other evaluations:\n91: \n92: - Most efficient open-source library in *ScrapingHub*'s [article extraction benchmark](https://github.com/scrapinghub/article-extraction-benchmark)\n93: - Best overall tool according to [Bien choisir son outil d'extraction de contenu à partir du Web](https://hal.archives-ouvertes.fr/hal-02768510v3/document)\n94:   (Lejeune & Barbaresi 2020)\n95: - Best single tool by ROUGE-LSum Mean F1 Page Scores in [An Empirical Comparison of Web Content Extraction Algorithms](https://webis.de/downloads/publications/papers/bevendorff_2023b.pdf)\n96:   (Bevendorff et al. 2023)\n97: \n98: \n99: ## Usage and documentation\n100: \n101: [Getting started with Trafilatura](https://trafilatura.readthedocs.io/en/latest/quickstart.html)\n102: is straightforward. For more information and detailed guides, visit\n103: [Trafilatura's documentation](https://trafilatura.readthedocs.io/):\n104: \n105: - [Installation](https://trafilatura.readthedocs.io/en/latest/installation.html)\n106: - Usage:\n107:   [On the command-line](https://trafilatura.readthedocs.io/en/latest/usage-cli.html),\n108:   [With Python](https://trafilatura.readthedocs.io/en/latest/usage-python.html),\n109:   [With R](https://trafilatura.readthedocs.io/en/latest/usage-r.html)\n110: - [Core Python functions](https://trafilatura.readthedocs.io/en/latest/corefunctions.html)\n111: - Interactive Python Notebook: [Trafilatura Overview](docs/Trafilatura_Overview.ipynb)\n112: - [Tutorials and use cases](https://trafilatura.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorials.html)\n113: \n114: Youtube playlist with video tutorials in several languages:\n115: \n116: - [Web scraping tutorials and how-tos](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8GkiOM17t0Q&list=PL-pKWbySIRGMgxXQOtGIz1-nbfYLvqrci)\n117: \n118: \n119: ## License\n120: \n121: This package is distributed under the [Apache 2.0 license](https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0.html).\n122: \n123: Versions prior to v1.8.0 are under GPLv3+ license.\n124: \n125: \n126: ### Contributing\n127: \n128: Contributions of all kinds are welcome. Visit the [Contributing\n129: page](https://github.com/adbar/trafilatura/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md)\n130: for more information. Bug reports can be filed on the [dedicated issue\n131: page](https://github.com/adbar/trafilatura/issues).\n132: \n133: Many thanks to the\n134: [contributors](https://github.com/adbar/trafilatura/graphs/contributors)\n135: who extended the docs or submitted bug reports, features and bugfixes!\n136: \n137: \n138: ## Context\n139: \n140: This work started as a PhD project at the crossroads of linguistics and\n141: NLP, this expertise has been instrumental in shaping Trafilatura over\n142: the years. Initially launched to create text databases for research purposes\n143: at the Berlin-Brandenburg Academy of Sciences (DWDS and ZDL units),\n144: this package continues to be maintained but its future depends on community support.\n145: \n146: **If you value this software or depend on it for your product, consider\n147: sponsoring it and contributing to its codebase**. Your support\n148: [on GitHub](https://github.com/sponsors/adbar) or [ko-fi.com](https://ko-fi.com/adbarbaresi)\n149: will help maintain and enhance this popular package.\n150: \n151: *Trafilatura* is an Italian word for [wire\n152: drawing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wire_drawing) symbolizing the\n153: refinement and conversion process. It is also the way shapes of pasta\n154: are formed.\n155: \n156: ### Author\n157: \n158: Reach out via ia the software repository or the [contact\n159: page](https://adrien.barbaresi.eu/) for inquiries, collaborations, or\n160: feedback. See also social networks for the latest updates.\n161: \n162: -   Barbaresi, A. [Trafilatura: A Web Scraping Library and Command-Line\n163:     Tool for Text Discovery and\n164:     Extraction](https://aclanthology.org/2021.acl-demo.15/), Proceedings\n165:     of ACL/IJCNLP 2021: System Demonstrations, 2021, p. 122-131.\n166: -   Barbaresi, A. \"[Generic Web Content Extraction with Open-Source\n167:     Software](https://hal.archives-ouvertes.fr/hal-02447264/document)\",\n168:     Proceedings of KONVENS 2019, Kaleidoscope Abstracts, 2019.\n169: -   Barbaresi, A. \"[Efficient construction of metadata-enhanced web\n170:     corpora](https://hal.archives-ouvertes.fr/hal-01371704v2/document)\",\n171:     Proceedings of the [10th Web as Corpus Workshop\n172:     (WAC-X)](https://www.sigwac.org.uk/wiki/WAC-X), 2016.\n173: \n174: \n175: ### Citing Trafilatura\n176: \n177: Trafilatura is widely used in the academic domain, chiefly for data\n178: acquisition. Here is how to cite it:\n179: \n180: [![Reference DOI: 10.18653/v1/2021.acl-demo.15](https://img.shields.io/badge/DOI-10.18653%2Fv1%2F2021.acl--demo.15-blue)](https://aclanthology.org/2021.acl-demo.15/)\n181: [![Zenodo archive DOI: 10.5281/zenodo.3460969](https://zenodo.org/badge/DOI/10.5281/zenodo.3460969.svg)](https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3460969)\n182: \n183: ``` shell\n184: @inproceedings{barbaresi-2021-trafilatura,\n185:   title = {{Trafilatura: A Web Scraping Library and Command-Line Tool for Text Discovery and Extraction}},\n186:   author = \"Barbaresi, Adrien\",\n187:   booktitle = \"Proceedings of the Joint Conference of the 59th Annual Meeting of the Association for Computational Linguistics and the 11th International Joint Conference on Natural Language Processing: System Demonstrations\",\n188:   pages = \"122--131\",\n189:   publisher = \"Association for Computational Linguistics\",\n190:   url = \"https://aclanthology.org/2021.acl-demo.15\",\n191:   year = 2021,\n192: }\n193: ```\n194: \n195: \n196: ### Software ecosystem\n197: \n198: Jointly developed plugins and additional packages also contribute to the\n199: field of web data extraction and analysis:\n200: \n201: <img alt=\"Software ecosystem\" src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/adbar/htmldate/master/docs/software-ecosystem.png\" align=\"center\" width=\"65%\"/>\n202: \n203: Corresponding posts can be found on [Bits of\n204: Language](https://adrien.barbaresi.eu/blog/tag/trafilatura.html).\n205: \n206: Impressive, you have reached the end of the page: Thank you for your\n207: interest!\n\n(End of file - total 207 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Trafilatura: Discover and Extract Text Data on the Web\n\n<br/>\n\n<img alt=\"Trafilatura Logo\" src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/adbar/trafilatura/master/docs/trafilatura-logo.png\" align=\"center\" width=\"60%\"/>\n\n<br/>\n\n[![Python package](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/trafilatura.svg)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/trafilatura)\n[![Python versions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/trafilatura.svg)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/trafilatura)\n[![Documentation Status](https://readthedocs.org/projects/trafilatura/badge/?version=latest)](http://trafilatura.readthedocs.org/en/latest/?badge=latest)\n[![Code Coverage](https://img.shields.io/codecov/c/github/adbar/trafilatura.svg)](https://codecov.io/gh/adbar/trafilatura)\n[![Downloads](https://static.pepy.tech/badge/trafilatura/month)](https://pepy.tech/project/trafilatura)\n[![Reference DOI: 10.18653/v1/2021.acl-demo.15](https://img.shields.io/badge/DOI-10.18653%2Fv1%2F2021.acl--demo.15-blue)](https://aclanthology.org/2021.acl-demo.15/)\n\n<br/>\n\n<img alt=\"Demo as GIF image\" src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/adbar/trafilatura/master/docs/trafilatura-demo.gif\" align=\"center\" width=\"80%\"/>\n\n<br/>","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"README.md","time":{"start":1775778161766,"end":1775778161777}}}]}
